cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques such as autoencoders and generative adversarial networks for anomaly detection, which are commonly used in the sub-fields of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of GANs for image reconstruction (cs.CV) and the need for robustness in detecting anomalies (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes a novel GAN architecture for improving anomaly detection, which falls under the sub-field of neural networks (cs.NE).
